{"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(_:)-3dal7","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(_:)-3g7pp","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(_:)-3sg1w","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(_:)-6iibg","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(_:)-8g8g2","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(object:object:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(opaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(raw:)-26247","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(raw:)-797bm","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(retaining:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(retainingCPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(retainingOpaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(retainingRaw:)-16wjq","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(retainingRaw:)-7dv4s","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(simple:data:)"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/ptr"],"title":"Instance Properties"},{"title":"Type Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/new(object:object:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/new(simple:data:)"]},{"title":"Default Implementations","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/ClosureProtocol-Implementations"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GClosure"},{"text":" represents a callback supplied by the programmer.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/closure"]}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"roleHeading":"Class","title":"Closure","externalID":"s:10GLibObject7ClosureC","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Closure","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"class","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Closure","kind":"identifier"}]},"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureProtocol","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP"],"type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Closure"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It will generally comprise a function of some kind and a marshaller"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"used to call it. It is the responsibility of the marshaller to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"convert the arguments for the invocation from ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GValues"},{"type":"text","text":" into"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"a suitable form, perform the callback on the converted arguments,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and transform the return value back into a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Value"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the case of C programs, a closure usually just holds a pointer","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to a function and maybe a data argument, and the marshaller"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"converts between "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Value","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and native C types. The GObject"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"library provides the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/CClosure","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" type for this purpose. Bindings for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"other languages need marshallers which convert between "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GValues"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and suitable representations in the runtime of the language in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"order to use functions written in that language as callbacks. Use"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_closure_set_marshal()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to set the marshaller on such a custom","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"closure implementation."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Within GObject, closures play an important role in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implementation of signals. When a signal is registered, the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"c_marshaller","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" argument to "},{"code":"g_signal_new()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" specifies the default C"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"marshaller for any closure which is connected to this","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"signal. GObject provides a number of C marshallers for this"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"purpose, see the g_cclosure_marshal_","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"() functions. Additional C"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"marshallers can be generated with the "},{"identifier":"#glib-genmarshal","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"utility.  Closures can be explicitly connected to signals with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_signal_connect_closure()"},{"type":"text","text":", but it usually more convenient to let"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"GObject create a closure automatically by using one of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"g_signal_connect_"}]},{"text":"() functions which take a callback function\/user","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"data pair.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Using closures has a number of important advantages over a simple","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"callback function\/data pointer combination:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Closures allow the callee to get the types of the callback parameters,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"which means that language bindings don’t have to write individual glue","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for each callback type.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The reference counting of ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" makes it easy to handle reentrancy"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"right; if a callback is removed while it is being invoked, the closure","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and its parameters won’t be freed until the invocation finishes."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_closure_invalidate()"},{"text":" and invalidation notifiers allow callbacks to be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"automatically removed when the objects they point to go away."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" type acts as a reference-counted owner of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GClosure"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure","isActive":true},{"text":" as a strong reference or owner of a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GClosure"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure","isActive":true},{"text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GClosure","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/Closure/init(retainingOpaquePointer:)":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Unsafe untyped, retai